    "Another variable to consider is that of user demand-might the performance of either version, particularly GPT-3.5, degrade with increased user demand at a given time?",
    "Next, we must also consider the limitations of the BERT NLP processing model with which we consolidated the ChatGPT responses into 50 themes.",
    "While the NLP model allows us to automate the consolidation process and reduce human error, and we employed the Davies-Bouldin Index, Silhouette, and Within-Cluster Sum of Squares scores (Supplementary Fig. 1), BERT is not perfect, and minor errors in clustering are possible, such as a group of temperature change topics including the more general topic of 'arctic change.'",
    "However, because BERT takes context into account, such an example may have related to temperature change in the original text.",
